<s> Finally, it may be that all this has been hashed out in considerable detail in the past (perhaps there are some position summaries in the W3C or IETF archives?) but the fact that class identifiers such as URL, URN, etc. "won't die" suggests that the contemporary view does not reflect the needs of the web community at large.  </s>
