<s> What's interesting is that, while I've always understood the W3C clarification as being a clarification of the *views* -- a tour of the classical and contemporary views and what each one asserts or presumes -- the folks who were involved in writing it seem to think that it rather is a mandate for adoption of the contemporary view.  </s>
